t: Praise*p ye the Lord.*s Praise the Lord,*s O my soul.
While*p I live will I praise the Lord:*s I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.
Put*p not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help.
His*p breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth; in that very day his thoughts perish.
Happy*p is he that hath the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is in the Lord*s his God:
Which*p made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that therein is: which keepeth truth for ever:
Which*p executeth judgment for the oppressed: which giveth food to the hungry. The Lord*s looseth the prisoners:
The*p Lord*s openeth the eyes of the blind: the Lord*s raiseth them that are bowed down: the Lord*s loveth the righteous:
The*p Lord*s preserveth the strangers; he relieveth the fatherless and widow: but the way of the wicked he turneth upside down.
The*p Lord*s shall reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the Lord.*s
